cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular languages and finite automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses complexity measures of regular languages. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the syntactic semigroup of regular languages. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the state complexity of regular languages. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of boolean operations in regular languages.
